reviews.text: Despite its location, loving hut is very serene and quiet - perfect for a cruelty-free escape. The menu features a wide variety of mostly Chinese vegan food, and they also have a nice selection of desserts. It’s so relaxing to spend time here.
I love this place so much! The food are so good with affordable price! Def one of my fave places!

Nice staff clean spacious

Huge space for the neighborhood, super fast WiFi, some power sockets. The set lunch is relatively bland, but healthy, affordable, and nutritious. Lots of dishes a la carte, plus desserts and a small grocery section. Everything 100% vegan. The ownership and backstory of the franchise is concerning, but easy to ignore.

If you're interested in vegan food this is perhaps one of the best restaurants for you in all of Hong Kong. Everything they have is vegan. The place is situated in a second floor and has enough room even at busy times. The food is tasty and has good prices. If you're looking for the most bang for your buck try the Lunch/Dinner menu. (1 rice +3 sides)
The staff will give you a free glass of water once you sit down to order, which is very much appreciated in a hot and busy place like Hong Kong.
